# security/auditsec/Kconfig
#
# Kconfig documentation: Documentation/kbuild/kconfig-language.rst
# How LSMs declare themselves: security/Kconfig (SECURITY_LOADABLE_LSMLIST)
#
# For in-tree integration:
#   1. Copy this block into security/Kconfig under the "LSM" menu
#   2. Add 'auditsec' to the LSM_ORDER list or use lsm= kernel param

config SECURITY_AUDITSEC
	tristate "auditsec audit-logging LSM"
	depends on SECURITY
	default n
	help
	  A teaching LSM that logs security-relevant events:
	  file opens, exec calls, socket creation, inode permission checks,
	  and signal delivery.

	  Operates in three modes (tunable via /sys/kernel/auditsec/enabled):
	    0 — silent (no logging, all hooks pass through)
	    1 — log-only (default): emit pr_info records, never deny
	    2 — enforce: deny exec() for the configured denied_uid

	  This module is intended for learning and should NOT be used
	  in production kernels.

	  If unsure, say N.

config SECURITY_AUDITSEC_FIXED
	tristate "auditsec (bug-fixed version)"
	depends on SECURITY
	default n
	help
	  Reference implementation with BUG-1 and BUG-2 corrected.
	  Use this to compare against the buggy version during study.

config SECURITY_AUDITSEC_RUST
	tristate "auditsec Rust LSM (requires CONFIG_RUST)"
	depends on SECURITY && RUST
	default n
	help
	  Rust language port of auditsec. Requires kernel built with
	  CONFIG_RUST=y and the rust/kernel/security.rs bindings.
	  As of v6.8 the Rust LSM trait bindings are in-flight;
	  check lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux for current status.
